<%= stream_react_component("CacheDemoPage",
                         prerender: true,
                         trace: true,
                         id: "CacheDemoPage-react-component-0") %>

<hr/>

<h2>About This Example</h2>
<p>
  This page demonstrates <code>unstable_cache</code> from React on Rails Pro.
  It wraps an async function that returns React Server Component output and
  caches the serialized RSC payload.
</p>
<p>
  <strong>How to verify caching:</strong> Refresh the page &mdash; the timestamps
  in the &ldquo;Cached Results&rdquo; section remain the same, while the
  &ldquo;Uncached&rdquo; timestamp changes every time.
</p>
<p>
  <strong>Tag invalidation:</strong> Call
  <code>ReactOnRailsPro::RSCCache.revalidate_tag("timestamps")</code> from a Rails
  console to clear the cached timestamps.
</p>
